  <span id="freeText1362256030769398100" style="display:none">The story continues from where Siddhant Roay's life is messed up completely. How he shapes up when problems galore and will he be able to overcome it all is a big question in the story? <br /><br />The narration does justice to the story but the depth is found wanting many times. The story lacks freshness and the only part that excites is struggle. The predictability factor is too high and there is nothing out of the blues to comfort the readers. <br /><br />The tell tale of a struggler is good and one can sympathize with it but the monotonous college scenes and overdose of booze and smoke kills the excitement. <br /><br />A good book but with lots to work upon for a concept and story line. </span>
